01:01:52.020 --> 01:01:56.650 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now let’s visit our brothers and sisters
in Colombia for this month’s postcard.

01:01:57.442 --> 01:02:00.862 line:90% position:50% align:center
Does Colombia
remind you of a certain beverage?

01:02:00.862 --> 01:02:03.532 line:90% position:50% align:center
It makes me think of coffee.

01:02:03.532 --> 01:02:07.035 line:90% position:50% align:center
Colombia is one of the world’s
largest coffee producers,

01:02:07.035 --> 01:02:09.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
since its soil, rainfall, and geography

01:02:09.955 --> 01:02:12.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
are ideal for growing arabica beans,

01:02:12.958 --> 01:02:15.586 line:90% position:50% align:center
known for their rich flavor and aroma.

01:02:16.503 --> 01:02:19.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
But more than coffee thrives here.

01:02:19.256 --> 01:02:23.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
Over 1,500 species of birds fill the air.

01:02:24.845 --> 01:02:28.473 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jaguars, monkeys, sloths, and tapirs

01:02:28.473 --> 01:02:30.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
roam the landscape.

01:02:30.475 --> 01:02:32.477 line:90% position:50% align:center
Burrowing just below the surface,

01:02:32.477 --> 01:02:36.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
earthworms grow up to 1.8 meters,
or 6 feet, in length.

01:02:38.233 --> 01:02:40.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
The truth took root in the 1920’s

01:02:40.569 --> 01:02:43.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
when Heliodoro Hernández
began reading <i>The Watchtower.</i>

01:02:44.906 --> 01:02:47.909 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first missionaries arrived in 1945.

01:02:49.411 --> 01:02:53.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the past, parts of the country
suffered from internal conflicts,

01:02:53.957 --> 01:02:56.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
and some remote areas
still experience their effects.

01:02:58.045 --> 01:03:00.714 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because our brothers maintained neutrality

01:03:00.714 --> 01:03:04.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
and wisely exercised caution in the ministry,

01:03:04.092 --> 01:03:06.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
the preaching work never stopped.

01:03:07.971 --> 01:03:11.516 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, more than 186,000 publishers

01:03:11.516 --> 01:03:16.355 line:90% position:50% align:center
zealously share the good news
with Colombia’s 51 million inhabitants.

01:03:17.356 --> 01:03:20.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our brothers preach
in 18 languages and dialects

01:03:20.567 --> 01:03:24.154 line:90% position:50% align:center
and can be found in every corner
of this diverse land

01:03:24.946 --> 01:03:27.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
in cities such as Manizales,

01:03:27.491 --> 01:03:30.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
Bogotá, Cartagena, and Medellín.

01:03:31.411 --> 01:03:35.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’ll see them preaching
in communities such as Villa de Leyva,

01:03:35.499 --> 01:03:38.835 line:90% position:50% align:center
rural areas like Neflandia, Córdoba,

01:03:38.835 --> 01:03:40.671 line:90% position:50% align:center
on the island of Providencia

01:03:40.671 --> 01:03:43.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
and, yes, on coffee farms too.

01:03:44.466 --> 01:03:46.468 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here publishers are on their way to preach

01:03:46.468 --> 01:03:49.680 line:90% position:50% align:center
on an Embera Chamí indigenous reservation.

01:03:51.306 --> 01:03:55.018 line:90% position:50% align:center
In addition to the ministry,
our brothers enjoy association,

01:03:55.018 --> 01:03:58.355 line:90% position:50% align:center
music, dancing,
and delicious Colombian dishes,

01:03:58.355 --> 01:04:01.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
such as <i>arepas, bandeja paisa,</i> and <i>sancocho</i>.

01:04:03.026 --> 01:04:05.946 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our brothers and sisters in Colombia,

01:04:05.946 --> 01:04:09.658 line:90% position:50% align:center
including the Bethel family,
send you their warm love and greetings.

01:04:11.410 --> 01:04:15.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
And please remember
that we too cherish each one of you

01:04:15.539 --> 01:04:18.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
as part of our precious international family.

